description: Numbers that are divisible only by primes congruent to 2 mod 3.
comments: Square roots of numbers n such that n-th coefficient of eta(x)^3/eta(x^3)=-1, where eta(x) is given by A010815. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Oct 06 2005
links: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..10000
prog: (MAGMA) [n: n in [1..300] | forall{d: d in PrimeDivisors(n) | d mod 3 eq 2}]; // _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 21 2012
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
